# 26. Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array
# Difficulty: Easy
# Topic: Array, Two Pointers
# LeetCode: https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array/

"""
Problem
Given a sorted array nums, remove the duplicates in-place so that
each unique element appears only once.

Return the number of unique elements.

Definition
The array is already sorted, so duplicate elements will appear
next to each other.

We need to keep only the unique values at the beginning of the array.

Idea
Use two pointers:
- i → scans the array
- j → keeps track of the position where the next unique element should go

Approach
1. Start j at index 1 (first element is always unique).
2. Traverse the array using pointer i.
3. Compare nums[i] with the previous element nums[i-1].
4. If they are different:
   place nums[i] at nums[j].
5. Move j forward.

After the loop, the first j elements contain unique values.

Example
nums = [1,1,2]

Step result:
[1,2]

Return → 2

Time Complexity
O(n)

Space Complexity
O(1)
"""

class Solution(object):
    def removeDuplicates(self, nums):

        n = len(nums)
        j = 1

        for i in range(1, n):

            if nums[i] != nums[i-1]:
                nums[j] = nums[i]
                j += 1

        return j
